---
title: bsc:eth_getBlockByHash - Binance Smart Chain
description: Example code for the bsc:eth_getBlockByHash json-rpc method. Ð¡omplete guide on how to use bsc:eth_getBlockByHash json-rpc in GetBlock.io Web3 documentation.
---

### Parameters


`DATA` - hex string

32-byte hash of a block.

`Boolean` - boolean

If true, returns the full transaction objects; if false, returns the
transaction hashes.

### Request

``` java
curl --location --request POST 'https://bsc.getblock.io/mainnet/' 
--header 'x-api-key: YOUR-API-KEY' 
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' 
--data-raw '{"jsonrpc": "2.0",
"method": "eth_getBlockByHash",
"params": ["0x1ed2922c46eaa5f285612e39d1a4e0fea317cddb3a18177c3359982587e28c3b", false],
"id": "getblock.io"}'
```
